INTRODUCTION
------------

Wingo server is a the backend API for wingo application. This is a python3 web application using Flask library. For a full description, visit the gitlab.labsquare.org/wingo-server . 

REQUIREMENTS
------------
Wingo server required python 3 and several library avaible from requirements.txt.
Mongo Database is required. Install it by following instruction from https://www.mongodb.org/.

INSTALLATION
------------
* Setup virtualenv 
From the repertory, create a virtual environement for python3 using virtualenv command : 

	virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python3 venv 

Activate the virtual environement by runing "activate" from venv directory 

	source venv/bin/activate 

Check if you have the right python version, which must be Python 3.4

	python --version 

* Install dependency using pip. All libary will installed into your virtual environement

	pip install -r requirements.txt 

CONFIGURATION
------------

* Setup mongo database connexion
First check if you have a mongodb instance running. You can use the software robomongo avaible from http://robomongo.org/. 
By default, wingo server use devel settings avaible in config/devel. You can edit it to setup the database connexion.  

* Fill database 
To fill the database with fake data , just type : 

	python manage.py generate 

* Run the wingo server 
To launch the server, just type : 

	python manage.py runserver 


TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------
If you get any error during this process step, please create a new issue from http://gitlab.labsquare.org 


